OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1780617775
OL,3,CAndrew Mountbatten-Windsor earned
OL,4,Cincome from Royal Lodge cottage sublets
OL,6,FThe former prince, Andrew Mountbatten-
OL,7,FWindsor, has been earning money by
OL,8,Fsubletting properties in the grounds
OL,9,Fof his former home in Windsor.
OL,11,FThe arrangements for the lease of his
OL,12,Fhome, Royal Lodge, from which he was
OL,13,Fejected by the King last year, have
OL,14,Fbeen revealed in a new report, which
OL,15,Falso shows his daughters don't pay any
OL,16,Frent on their homes inside royal
OL,17,Fpalaces.
OL,19,FPrincess Beatrice and Eugenie have
OL,20,Ftheir rent paid for them by their
OL,21,Funcle, King Charles.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1780617775
OL,3,CAndrew Mountbatten-Windsor earned
OL,4,Cincome from Royal Lodge cottage sublets
OL,6,FThe King pays it from his private
OL,7,Fincome, which means the sisters don't
OL,8,Fpay any money themselves, despite
OL,9,Fhaving jobs and not being working
OL,10,Fmembers of the Royal Family.
OL,12,FThe arrangements for Mountbatten-
OL,13,FWindsor, as Andrew is now known, were
OL,14,Frevealed after an investigation into
OL,15,Froyal properties and leases by the
OL,16,FNational Audit Office.
OL,18,FIt has revealed, for the first time,
OL,19,Fthat the disgraced Prince was
OL,20,Freceiving an income by sub-letting
OL,21,Fthree cottages within Royal Lodge.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1780617775
OL,3,CAndrew Mountbatten-Windsor earned
OL,4,Cincome from Royal Lodge cottage sublets
OL,6,FWe already knew that Andrew was paying
OL,7,Fonly a 'peppercorn' rent at the
OL,8,Fmansion after agreeing a lease with
OL,9,Fthe landlords, The Crown Estate, in
OL,10,F2003.
OL,12,FThe National Audit Office started
OL,13,Flooking into royal properties to
OL,14,Fassist MPs on the Public Accounts
OL,15,FCommittee who wanted to know who was
OL,16,Fpaying what and why.
OL,18,FInvestigators then discovered that
OL,19,FAndrew's lease allowed him to sublet
OL,20,Fthree of the eight cottages in the
OL,21,Fgrounds of the home.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
