CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1780617775
OL,3,CAndrew Mountbatten-Windsor earned
OL,4,Cincome from Royal Lodge cottage sublets
OL,6,FHis daughters, meanwhile, who are not
OL,7,Fconsidered 'working' Royals and have
OL,8,Ftheir own careers, are effectively
OL,9,Fallowed to live rent-free in royal
OL,10,Fresidences after King Charles agreed
OL,11,Fto stick with an arrangement Queen
OL,12,FElizabeth had agreed with her
OL,13,Fgranddaughters.
OL,15,FCharles pays for the accommodation for
OL,16,FBeatrice in St James Palace and
OL,17,FEugenie in Ivy Cottage, Kensington
OL,18,FPalace, from his own private income,
OL,19,Fcalled the Privy Purse, which means it
OL,20,Fdoes not come out of public funds.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1780617775
OL,3,CAndrew Mountbatten-Windsor earned
OL,4,Cincome from Royal Lodge cottage sublets
OL,6,FNevertheless, there will be questions
OL,7,Fabout why they get to keep these
OL,8,Farrangements when they don't
OL,9,Fcontribute to the operation of the
OL,10,FBritish Monarchy.
OL,12,FThe King also pays the rent for Prince
OL,13,Fand Princess Michael of Kent, who are
OL,14,Falso non-working Royals and now in
OL,15,Ftheir 80s.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
